The paper deals with unsupervised audiovisual synthesis, which involves both speech and video data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also involves generating video from audio signals and vice versa, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper uses autoencoders, which are commonly used in the fields of cs.SD and cs.CV. The paper also involves learning the specific style of a target speaker, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in the field of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
